<br>
As such, Rain spells are more efficent, but &quot;resist&quot; more (when they're really just &quot;missing&quot;)<br>
<br>
Explains resists on greens<br>
Explains resist rate on other mobs <p>Salash Penumbra - Summoner of Armies!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urhionsligo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 639<br> <font color=#333333>(6/21/02 2:33:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1361.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/starofdavid.gif width=36 height=37></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Here comes the rain again...</span><hr size=1> Salash, you can come up with a roleplaying reason for anything in a fantasy video game. <p><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg" align="center"><br>
